\f0\fs24 \cf0 yes,lets tighten dev-prod\
\
Here\'92s a tightened, current **Dev \uc0\u8594  Prod** runbook that matches how things are actually wired now (`nexus-dev-postgres` for dev, `nexusprod-v2` for prod, Cloud Run + Vercel).\
\
I\'92ll keep this as a single \'93source of truth\'94 you can follow every time.\
\
---\
\
## 0. Environment definitions\
\
- **Dev DB**: `nexus-dev-postgres` (Cloud SQL)\
- **Prod DB**: `nexusprod-v2` (Cloud SQL)\
- **Cloud Run (prod)**:\
  - API: `nexus-api`\
  - Worker: `nexus-worker`\
- **Cloud Run (dev)**:\
  - API dev: `nexus-api-dev`\
- **Web (prod)**:\
  - Vercel app (points to `https://nexus-api-979156454944.us-central1.run.app`)\
\
---\
\
## 1. Local dev: canonical startup (dev DB)\
\
Use this whenever you sit down to develop.\
\
```bash\
cd ~/nexus-enterprise\
\
# 1) Ensure dev DB proxy is running (nexus-dev-postgres on 5433)\
cloud-sql-proxy --port=5433 nexus-enterprise-480610:us-central1:nexus-dev-postgres\
# leave this running in its own terminal\
\
# 2) In a new terminal: start clean dev env (API + worker + web)\
export DEV_DB_PASSWORD='NEXUS_2025_DEV-v2'\
./scripts/dev-clean-env.sh\
```\
- API dev: `http://localhost:8000`\
- Web dev: `http://localhost:3000`\
- Dev DB: `nexus-dev-postgres` via proxy on 5433.\
\
Check:\
\
```bash\
curl -i http://localhost:8000/health\
# expect 200 + \{"ok":true,"redis":"unreachable"\} in dev (no-op Redis)\
```\
---\
\
## 2. Normal dev workflow (code + schema)\
\
1. **Code changes** in `apps/api`, `apps/web`, `packages/database`, etc.\
2. **Schema changes** (against dev DB only):\
\
```bash\
   cd ~/nexus-enterprise/packages/database\
\
   export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:$\{DEV_DB_PASSWORD\}@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db"\
\
   # edit prisma/schema.prisma\
\
   npx prisma migrate dev --name <migration_name> --schema ./prisma/schema.prisma\
```\
3. Run tests / manual checks against dev stack (web at `http://localhost:3000`).\
\
Once you\'92re happy with behavior on **dev DB**, you\'92re allowed to go to prod.\
\
---\
\
## 3. Prod DB migrations (nexusprod-v2)\
\
**Only** when your Prisma migrations are ready to ship.\
\
1. Start Cloud SQL proxy to prod instance:\
\
```bash\
   cloud-sql-proxy --port=5433 nexus-enterprise-480610:us-central1:nexusprod-v2\
   # leave running in its own terminal\
```\
2. Apply migrations with prod `DATABASE_URL`:\
\
```bash\
   cd ~/nexus-enterprise\
\
   export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:<PROD_DB_PASSWORD>@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db"\
\
   ./scripts/db-migrate-prod.sh\
```\
   - This runs `prisma migrate deploy` in `packages/database` against **nexusprod-v2**.\
   - Expect: \'93No pending migrations\'94 or a list of applied migrations and `[db-migrate-prod] Done.`\
\
---\
\
## 4. Deploy API to prod (`nexus-api`)\
\
From repo root:\
\
```bash\
cd ~/nexus-enterprise\
./scripts/deploy-api.sh\
```\
This:\
\
- Builds the Docker image with `turbo build --filter=api`.\
- Pushes it to Artifact Registry.\
- Deploys a new Cloud Run revision for `nexus-api` (already wired to `nexusprod-v2` + Redis).\
\
Verify:\
\
```bash\
curl -i https://nexus-api-979156454944.us-central1.run.app/health\
# expect 200 + \{"ok":true,"redis":"PONG"\}\
```\
If `/health` is not 200, **stop here** and fix API/DB before touching web or worker.\
\
---\
\
## 5. Deploy worker to prod (`nexus-worker`)\
\
Whenever API code or DB schema that the worker uses changes, bump the worker too:\
\
```bash\
gcloud run deploy nexus-worker \\\
  --image us-docker.pkg.dev/nexus-enterprise-480610/nexus-api/nexus-api \\\
  --platform managed \\\
  --region us-central1 \\\
  --project nexus-enterprise-480610 \\\
  --command node \\\
  --args dist/worker-http.js\
```\
- Service is already wired to `nexusprod-v2` and `REDIS_URL=redis://10.53.145.123:6379`.\
- This just moves it to the new image.\
\
---\
\
## 6. Web prod deploy (Vercel)\
\
Vercel is already configured to:\
\
- Pull from your Git branch.\
- Build `apps/web`.\
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://nexus-api-979156454944.us-central1.run.app`.\
\
Typical flow:\
\
1. **Commit & push** your changes (API, web, database migrations, scripts).\
2. Vercel automatically builds and deploys the web app.\
3. Once the Vercel build is done, visit the prod URL and log in.\
\
---\
\
## 7. Post-deploy smoke tests (prod)\
\
After each release, run this minimal checklist:\
\
1. **API health (prod)**\
\
```bash\
   curl -i https://nexus-api-979156454944.us-central1.run.app/health\
   # Must be 200 and redis: "PONG"\
```\
2. **Direct login (prod)**\
\
```bash\
   curl -i "https://nexus-api-979156454944.us-central1.run.app/auth/login" \\\
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\\
     -d '\{\
       "email": "paul@nfsgrp.com",\
       "password": "<PROD_PASSWORD>"\
     \}'\
```\
   - Expect 200/201 and JSON with `user`, `company`, `accessToken`, `refreshToken`.\
\
3. **Web login (prod)**\
\
   - Open Vercel URL \uc0\u8594  `/login`.\
   - Log in as `paul@nfsgrp.com` with prod password.\
   - Confirm dashboard loads and basic navigation works.\
\
4. **Worker sanity (optional but good)**\
\
   - Kick off a small import or background job you trust.\
   - Confirm it moves from QUEUED \uc0\u8594  RUNNING \u8594  SUCCEEDED in the DB.\
\
---\
\
## 8. Safe-guards / \'93do not do\'94 list\
\
- Don\'92t run `prisma migrate dev` against prod \'97 **only `migrate deploy`** with prod `DATABASE_URL`.\
- Don\'92t point local dev at `nexusprod-v2` for experiments; use `nexus-dev-postgres`.\
- Don\'92t run ad-hoc scripts with `PrismaClient` unless `DATABASE_URL` is explicitly set to the intended DB (dev or prod).\
- Always fix `/health` = 500 **before** debugging login issues.\
\
